  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dbd\u0ddd\u0d9a \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0d8b\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0db8\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda 5\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka ranks 5th in world food inflation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Bank announced that Sri Lanka has been among the top 10 countries most affected by inflation in the world's top food category.",
        "Accordingly, Sri Lanka was able to occupy the fifth place in the World Bank index of countries with the highest food inflation in the world.",
        "The four countries above Sri Lanka in that index are Lebanon, Zimbabwe, Venezuela and Turkey.",
        "According to Sri Lanka's National Consumer Price Index, the annual point inflation of the food category was recorded as 75.8 percent in June last year, and it has risen to 82.5 percent in July, according to the data reports of the Department of Population and Statistics."
      ],
